-- U.S. Awards $22.5 Million to Groups Developing Algae Biofuels
-- B y   J u s t i n   D o o m
-- 2013-08-01T21:57:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-01/u-s-awards-22-5-million-to-groups-developing-algae-biofuels.html
The U.S. Energy Department awarded
about $22.5 million in grants to companies and researchers
seeking to produce fuel from algae and other types of biomass.  Hawaii BioEnergy LLC, Sapphire Energy Inc. and New Mexico
State University each will receive $5 million to develop algae-based fuel technologies, according to a statement today on the
department’s website.  California Polytechnic State University will get $1.5
million to develop more producive algae. FDC Enterprises Inc.
will get about $6 million to improve processes for collecting
and distributing wood, grass and agricultural waste that’s
converted into fuel.  To contact the reporter on this story:
